# https://github.com/GoogleContainerTools/jib/tree/master/jib-maven-plugin#system-properties
- build docker image via jib:
mvn -DskipTest=true compile jib:build \
    -Djib.container.environment=ESDB_HOST="$ESDB_PROD_HOST"
or
mvn -X -Djib.serialize=true -Djib.console=plain compile jib:build \
    -Djib.container.environment=ESDB_HOST=$ESDB_PROD_HOST

Process:
MAKE SURE TO COMPLETED FOLLOWING STEPS BEFORE TAGGING IN GIT
1. Build and push new docker image via jib
2. Apply new k8s deployments
3. If this is a change in any api endpoint, don't forget to make the changes in openapi file.
4. Deploy endpoints config: gcloud endpoints services deploy openapi.yaml --project=zl-infra-main
See https://cloud.google.com/endpoints/docs/openapi/get-started-kubernetes#configuring_the_service_name_and_starting_the_service